[stdout] {"type":"text","timestamp":1772607698383,"sessionID":"ses_3485d8184ffeIMBvkfntWmAknR","part":{"id":"prt_cb7a6dd8700179qEE6LuY6V9Pv","sessionID":"ses_3485d8184ffeIMBvkfntWmAknR","messageID":"msg_cb7a6d197001YhyeA8vSe2DIDb","type":"text","text":"Implemented a minimal RP2040 breakout in `index.circuit.tsx` with autorouting disabled via `routingDisabled`, using only local/JLCPCB-imported components and no tscircuit registry package components.\n\n- Added JLCPCB-imported components:\n  - `imports/RP2040.tsx` (`C2040`)\n  - `imports/TYPE_C_31_M_12.tsx` (`C165948`)\n  - `imports/KT_0603R.tsx` (`C2286`)\n- Built a compact breakout board in `index.circuit.tsx` with:\n  - RP2040 MCU (`U1`)\n  - USB-C connector (`J_USB`)\n  - LED + series resistor (`D1`, `R_LED`)\n  - Two 1x8 headers (`J1`, `J2`) exposing GPIOs and power pins\n  - CC pull-down resistors for USB-C sink behavior (`R_CC1`, `R_CC2`)\n  - Basic decoupling / VREG capacitor (`C_3V3`, `C_VREG`)\n- Disabled autorouting at board level using `<board ... routingDisabled>`.\n- Used net-based connectivity so the design validates cleanly with routing disabled.\n- Ran the required build command: `tsci build --site --use-cdn-javascript` and it completed successfully, generating output in `dist/` (including `dist/index/circuit.json`).\n\nAssumptions used:\n- `net.V3_3` is provided externally on header pins for this minimal breakout.\n- The design is intentionally minimal and not a production-ready full RP2040 reference implementation.","time":{"start":1772607698381,"end":1772607698381}}}

